          "cheatSheet": "Precedence: +,- is 1; *,/ is 2; ^ is 3.\nPop operators of higher/equal precedence from stack to output before pushing current operator.",
          "code": "import java.util.Stack;\n\npublic class InfixToPostfix {\n    private static int prec(char ch) {\n        switch (ch) {\n            case '+': case '-': return 1;\n            case '*': case '/': return 2;\n            case '^': return 3;\n        }\n        return -1;\n    }\n    \n    public static String convert(String expr) {\n        // Input: Infix expression string\n        StringBuilder result = new StringBuilder(); // Storage\n        Stack<Character> stack = new Stack<>();     // Storage\n        \n        // Process: Operator precedence checking loops\n        for (int i = 0; i < expr.length(); ++i) {\n            char c = expr.charAt(i);\n            \n            if (Character.isLetterOrDigit(c)) {\n                result.append(c);\n            } else if (c == '(') {\n                stack.push(c);\n            } else if (c == ')') {\n                while (!stack.isEmpty() && stack.peek() != '(') {\n                    result.append(stack.pop());\n                }\n                stack.pop();\n            } else {\n                while (!stack.isEmpty() && prec(c) <= prec(stack.peek())) {\n                    result.append(stack.pop());\n                }\n                stack.push(c);\n            }\n        }\n        \n        while (!stack.isEmpty()) {\n            result.append(stack.pop());\n        }\n        // Output: Postfix string\n        return result.toString();\n    }\n}",
